METHODS: Results of the Global Burden of Disease Study 2010 (GBD 2010) were used 
to demonstrate the burden of infectious disease of the Chinese population in 
1990 and 2010 and changing pattern from 1990 to 2010 by gender and age groups, 
including indicators of incidence, mortality, years of life lost due to 
premature mortality (YLL), years lived with disability (YLD), 
disability-adjusted life years (DALY), and their age-standardized rates using 
data of the 2010 National Census as a standard population.
RESULTS: In 1990 incidence, standardized incidence rate, mortality, standardized 
